{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"fd4a21eb-9166-438a-a44f-686132a6872a","content":"Good news — in .NET 10, `dotnet test` uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform **by default**. You no longer need `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport`; that was the .NET 9 opt-in. You can safely remove it.\n\n`EnableMSTestRunner` is still required — it makes your test project build as an executable that hosts the MTP runner.\n\nHere's the cleanup:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01NELMLwbFDa9gkJghnM7APp","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-ccea8f54ae9b4e6aa9e0ba2f92bff4fa/TestProject.csproj","old_str":"    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n    <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>","new_str":"    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-ccea8f54ae9b4e6aa9e0ba2f92bff4fa/TestProject.csproj."}],"interactionId":"defb8851-dee9-4e1c-8074-ce96dc05afc3","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is on .NET 10 SDK with MSTest and Microsoft.Testing.Platform. In .NET 10, `dotnet test` natively uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) as the default runner, so:\n\n1. `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` is no longer needed — it was required in .NET 9 to opt in to MTP support, but .NET 10 uses MTP by default.\n2. `EnableMSTestRunner` is still needed to produce a standalone test executable using MSTest runner.\n\nLet me clean up their project file.","outputTokens":424,"requestId":"0433:3FE43:1FAEB58:2384610:69E81B26"},"id":"14f988d4-22d6-4a2f-94db-7c4d17479334","timestamp":"2026-04-22T00:49:49.265Z","parentId":"f776c4bc-113e-4894-8c46-04c5adfb4cf0"}
